author: Claudia Bauer
title: New York dance-maker goes West Coast
text:
Photo: Lea Suzuki, The Chronicle Risa Jaroslow, of Risa Jaroslow and Dancers, talks with dancers as during rehearsal for Resist/Surrender on Monday, October 5, 2015 in Oakland, Calif. Risa Jaroslow, of Risa Jaroslow and Dancers, talks with dancers as...
From Gold Rush prospectors to Beat poets to techies, San Francisco has always been a destination for pioneers and freedom-seekers. Among the most recent arrivals is veteran choreographer Risa Jaroslow, an expatriate New Yorker with postmodern bona fides and a thirst for adventure. Risa Jaroslow, of Risa Jaroslow and Dancers, talks with dancers as during rehearsal for Resist/Surrender on Monday, October 5, 2015 in Oakland, Calif.
